@Tricia G: As of this morning the Tory Government has a working majority of 1. This means that a Vote of No Confidence could be passed if a single defector were to vote against the government. If this vote is not rescinded within 14 days then a General Election must be called.
What’s actually interesting here is the timing of it all. Parliament re-convenes on the 3rd of September. Assuming a vote of no-confidence could be held and passed the following day then the earliest the Government could fall is the 18th. Further assuming that the minimum 6 week waiting period is followed then the earliest date for the election would be Wednesday October 30th.
All of which means that there is a very tight time-frame for the Opposition to squeeze in an election before Brexit is due to come into effect. Under normal circumstances I would say it’s impossible but I suspect there may be enough political will to avoid a Hard Brexit that they might still try.

